{"cursor":"2716","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\nIn theoretical physics, a 'preferred' or 'privileged frame' is usually a special\nhypothetical frame of reference in which the laws of physics might appear to be\nidentifiably different (simpler) from those in other frames.\n\nIn theories that apply the principle of relativity to inertial motion, physics\nis the same in all inertial frames, and is even the same in all frames under the\ngeneral principle of relativity.\n","linknr":105,"url":"Preferred_frame","recorded":1362567387,"links":13,"instances":[],"pdf":[],"categories":["Special relativity","Aether theories","Frames of reference"],"headings":["Preferred frame in aether theory","Inertial frames preferred above noninertial frames","See also","References"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/50px-Question_book-new.svg.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[],"members":[],"related":["Theoretical_physics","Hypothetical","Frame_of_reference","Laws_of_physics","Principle_of_relativity","Inertial_frame","Luminiferous_aether","Michelson-Morley_experiment","Null_result","Lorentz_aether_theory","Galilean_transformation","Lorentz_transformation","Special_relativity","Newtonian_mechanics","Special_relativity","Tests_of_special_relativity","Modern_searches_for_Lorentz_violation","Cosmic_microwave_background_radiation","Test_theories_of_special_relativity"]}